      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S is a museum-grade example of the 996-generation wide-body. It features the 3.6L flat-six engine paired with a 6-speed manual transaxle and a permanent all-wheel-drive system utilizing a viscous coupling. The chassis dynamics are enhanced by the factory Turbo-spec suspension and Brembo four-piston monoblock calipers. This vehicle is in pristine condition, with a documented service history confirming a proactive dual-row ceramic IMS bearing upgrade and a recent rear main seal replacement. The Arctic Silver Metallic finish is flawless, showing no road rash or oxidation, while the Metropol Blue leather interior remains supple with no bolster wear. Mechanically, the power plant is in peak health with consistent compression and no signs of bore scoring. A turn-key, collector-quality specimen for the serious purist.",
